In [11]:
checking = []

def checking_values (df):

    for col in df.columns:
        dtypes = df[col].dtypes
        null = df[col].isna().sum()
        notna = df[col].notnull().sum()
        unique = df[col].nunique()
        checking.append([col ,dtypes, null, notna, unique])
   
    check = pd.DataFrame(checking)
    check.columns = ['col', 'dtypes', 'null', 'notna', 'unique']

    return check

checking_values(df)

fig, axs = plt.subplots(5, 2, figsize=(25,25), sharex = True)
plt.suptitle('Top-10 GDP-Per Capita - After 2000', fontsize=20, weight = 'bold')
axs = axs.flatten()
i = 0 

for country in top_10['country_name'].unique():
     
    ax2 = axs[i].twinx()

    top_10[top_10['country_name'] == country].\
    plot(x='year', y='gdp_per_capita',\
    ax=axs[i])
          
    top_10[top_10['country_name'] == country]\
    .plot(x='year', y='avg_years_of_schooling',\
    ax=ax2, color='red')
      
    axs[i].set_ylabel('GDP per Capita', fontsize=12, color = 'blue')
    ax2.set_ylabel('Years of Schooling', fontsize = 12, color = 'red')
    axs[i].set_title(country)
    axs[i].grid(False)
    ax2.grid(False)
    
    i = i + 1
        
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
